# CODEOWNERS for SCS Specification
#
# This file defines who reviews different parts of the repository.
# On GitHub, these users will be automatically requested for review when
# a PR touches files matching the patterns below.
#
# More info: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything (unless overridden below)
* @timmccrimmon

# Specification documents - require maintainer review
/spec/ @timmccrimmon

# Schemas - require maintainer review (critical for validation)
/schema/ @timmccrimmon

# Governance documents - require maintainer review
/GOVERNANCE.md @timmccrimmon
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md @timmccrimmon
/LICENSE.md @timmccrimmon

# RFC process - maintainer decides
/rfcs/ @timmccrimmon

# Templates can have broader review
/templates/ @timmccrimmon

# Documentation - can add other reviewers here as team grows
/docs/ @timmccrimmon

# Examples - can add other reviewers here
/examples/ @timmccrimmon

# Tools - can add other reviewers here when you have tool contributors
/tools/ @timmccrimmon

# Configuration and CI - require maintainer review
/.github/ @timmccrimmon
